  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): 0.2.10+commit.418c85b\r\n* OS: linux\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): 3.8.5\r\n* Environment (output of `pip freeze`):\r\n\r\n```\r\napipkg==1.5\r\nasttokens==2.0.4\r\nattrs==20.3.0\r\nbase58==2.0.1\r\nbitarray==1.2.2\r\nblake2b-py==0.1.3\r\ncached-property==1.5.2\r\ncertifi==2020.12.5\r\nchardet==4.0.0\r\ncoverage==5.3.1\r\ncytoolz==0.11.0\r\neth-abi==2.1.1\r\neth-account==0.5.4\r\neth-bloom==1.0.3\r\neth-hash==0.2.0\r\neth-keyfile==0.5.1\r\neth-keys==0.3.3\r\neth-rlp==0.2.1\r\neth-tester==0.5.0b3\r\neth-typing==2.2.2\r\neth-utils==1.9.5\r\nexecnet==1.7.1\r\nhexbytes==0.2.1\r\nhypothesis==5.46.0\r\nidna==2.10\r\niniconfig==1.1.1\r\nipfshttpclient==0.7.0a1\r\njsonschema==3.2.0\r\nlark==0.11.1\r\nlru-dict==1.1.6\r\nmultiaddr==0.0.9\r\nmypy-extensions==0.4.3\r\nnetaddr==0.8.0\r\npackaging==20.8\r\nparsimonious==0.8.1\r\npluggy==0.13.1\r\nprotobuf==3.14.0\r\npy==1.10.0\r\npy-ecc==4.1.0\r\npy-evm==0.3.0a20\r\npycryptodome==3.9.9\r\npyethash==0.1.27\r\npyparsing==2.4.7\r\npyrsistent==0.17.3\r\npytest==6.2.1\r\npytest-cov==2.10.1\r\npytest-forked==1.3.0\r\npytest-xdist==2.2.0\r\nrequests==2.25.1\r\nrlp==2.0.1\r\nsemantic-version==2.8.5\r\nsix==1.15.0\r\nsortedcontainers==2.3.0\r\ntoml==0.10.2\r\ntoolz==0.11.1\r\ntrie==2.0.0a5\r\ntyping-extensions==3.7.4.3\r\nurllib3==1.26.2\r\nvarint==1.0.2\r\nvyper==0.2.10\r\nweb3==5.13.1\r\nwebsockets==8.1\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nIn Type Conversions section, the address is missing in supported types that can be converted. https://vyper.readthedocs.io/en/stable/types.html#type-conversions\r\n\r\nBut the compiler does not complain when I convert the address data type to other data type. The code below works.\r\n\r\n```\r\n@external\r\ndef __init__(a: address):\r\n    b : decimal = convert(a, decimal)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI haven't checked whether the conversion makes sense or not though. I'll update this bug report later.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nEither we update the document or we throw error when converting the address data type to other data type.",
